<TITLE> Court rejects HT Imam case </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 4 (bdnews24.com)  A Dhaka court has rejected a criminal case against HT Imam, a prime ministerial adviser, accusing him of hurting religious sentiments. Chief metropolitan magistrate Mostafa Shahriar Khan gave the order on Sunday on a petition filed by Supreme Court lawyer Mridha Md Rashed Sarwar Palash relating to a speech of Imam from two days ago. A correspondent from the news agency Focus Bangla, the publisher of Naya Diganta, a Bengali daily, Shamsul Huda and its editor Alamgir Mohiuddin are also named as defendants. The initial hearing will take place later in the day, Aminul Gani Tito, lawyer for the complainant, told bdnews24.com. The case relates to comments that Imam allegedly made when he addressed a meeting titled on war criminals in relation to Islam organised by the Awami Ulama League on Friday. In a Naya Diganta article, published the following day  quoting the news agency Focus Bangla  stated that Imam had said it was the Awami League which saved Islam in Bangladesh and that Bangabandhu Sheikh Mujibur Rahman introduced Islam to this country. In his petition to the court, the complainant claims that Imam's statement hurt religious sentiments and defamed the preacher and prophet of Islam, Muhammad (SM), and his followers. Four lawyers have been made witnesses to the case. bdn
